$Header: /u1/rcs/dte/book-format/README,v 1.1.2.6 1994/06/23 19:48:20 fred Exp $

Contents

    This directory contains the source for book-format and friends.
    These are short descriptions of the files:

    book-format.sh	Main wrapper to format a book.
    dman.sh		Stand-alone program to format one -man or rsml file.
    dmm.sh		Stand-alone program to format one -mm or gpsml file.
    dsml.sh		Stand-alone program to format one rsml or gpsml file.
    elimso.c		"soelim" equivalent, with minor enhancements.
    fix-man.sh		Mucks with header names in manpages in publish style.
    fixVertMot.c	Adjust some vertical movements.
    fmt-gloss.sh	Does the work for formatting a glossary.
    fmt-index.sh	Does the work for formatting a index.
    fmt-piece.sh	Does the work for formatting a piece of a book.
    fmt-toc.sh		Does the work for formatting a toc.
    forward.c		"col" equivalent.  Not built by default.
    includePS.sh	Used by .pI macro to include PS figures.
    indpostsort.c	Index processing (first stage).
    indpresort.c	Index processing (last stage).
    make-ptx.sh		Wrapper for making permuted index.
    query_gloss.c	Looks up words in glossary database, prints definitions.
    rmPic.sh		Removes pic code, if formatting with nroff. 
    rmboxes.sh		Removes boxes, if formatting with nroff. 
    rmifdef.c		Processes #ifdef's (similar to cpp).
    roff-cmd.c		Looks in source files to see what filters are needed.
    show-ifdefs.sh	Filter to embolden #ifdef/#endif's, for reviewers.
    sync-h1-man.sh	Deals with sync files.
    sync-h1-mm.sh	Deals with sync files.
    syncGen.sh		Deals with sync files.


Dependencies

    Q: What else is needed to run book-format?
    A: The data files in the macros and glossary directories.

